cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.NE, cs.IT 

This paper discusses decentralized stochastic optimization methods for machine learning applications, which are typically categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also touches upon control and signal processing applications, which fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of variance reduction techniques, which are commonly used in optimization problems in control systems (cs.SY) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses communication constraints, which are a common topic in information theory (cs.IT).
